Pulling back my recent adjustment.
Adjusting for decisiveness, granted my previous forecast is was probably as close as I was statistically going to get.
(I'm simply overweighting the favourite, although a lot could happen)
I made my first prediction before we had an exact list of the entrants, but now just 8 days out of the race we have preliminary lists coming out. From [1] the horses are:
Bet365 and Paddy Power dont have odds for Game Winner and Thunder Snow. Max Sec and McKinzie as favs
I've never thought about, let alone done a deep dive into the world of competitive horse racing. Looking at betting odds, articles and past performance, I feel this is a solid starting point.
It's the natural choice, if you know the right information.
I don't know them

First forecast based on [1], [2] and [3]. I'm not into horse racing so I don't have much to rely on. However, other factors such as the climate conditions and the form on the day are very much relevant and I haven't considered them so far.
Used ratings from https://www.horseracingnation.com/race/2020_Saudi_Cup#
What do I know about horses??? Nothing
McKinzie will find the nine furlongs of the Saudi Cup ideal. He has six Graded stakes from 13 tries, including four G1s.
If it’s in Saudi Arabia, it has to be Maximum Security.
Gut.

Disclaimer - not a horse racing aficionado, but fun to look at the potential factors here. Starting with the Saudi Cup website and looking at rating I pulled the recent results on the top horses, looking for head to head matchups, distances raced, times over distance, etc. Thanks to those who noted Thunder Snow's retirement. Game Winner is not currently listed on the Horseracing nation.com website as a contender in the Saudi Cup.
Following the bookie for top three

Report: Maximum Security to bypass Pegasus World Cup » Midnight Bisou ends 'mini-break,' working toward the Saudi Cup » Gronkowski 'going just right' into prep for big-money races https://www.horseracingnation.com/race/2020_Saudi_Cup#
Watching Musto Gusto though...
Gronk hasn't played in months so he'll be well rested

Thunder Snow has retired from racing.[1] Gronkowski came in second to Thunder Snow in the Dubai World Cup, last year.[2] McKinzie is the 5/1 favorite at the Dubai World Cup.[3] Midnight Bisou and Maximum Security are each contenders with 9/1 and 10/1 odds in the Dubai World Cup, respectively. Tacitus is not at the same level as these other horses.
Given that I could not find any list with the set of horses racing I'm going to spread my bets across the whole set. Will give a tighter prediction once we see the set of horses running.
I say it will be Maximum Security, Midnight Bisou, or Mucho Gusto.
